🟢 PHASE 0 – PROJECT & BASE SETUP
🎯 Goal

Create a clean backend + admin web foundation.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Create a full-stack project structure for a Preschool Management System.

Backend:
- Node.js + Express
- Environment variable support
- JWT authentication ready
- Connect to a cloud SQL database (MySQL or PostgreSQL)
- Use an ORM (Prisma or Sequelize)

Admin Web:
- React.js
- Ant Design UI
- Routing setup
- Authentication context

Create base folders for:
- auth
- users
- students
- parents
- classrooms
- attendance
- billing
- notifications

Ensure backend API is reusable for a future mobile application.

🟢 PHASE 1 – AUTHENTICATION & ROLE-BASED ACCESS (CRITICAL)
🎯 Goal

Secure login + roles (SuperAdmin, Admin, Teacher)

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement role-based authentication.

Requirements:
- User table with roles: SUPER_ADMIN, ADMIN, TEACHER
- Pre-seed one SUPER_ADMIN user in database
- Login API using username and password
- Password hashing using bcrypt
- JWT-based authentication
- Middleware for role-based route protection
- Force password change on first login

Admin Web:
- Login page using Ant Design
- After login, redirect based on role
- Block inactive users

Ensure this authentication system can also be used later by a mobile app.

🟢 PHASE 2 – MASTER DATA (PARENTS, CLASSROOMS, STAFF)
🎯 Goal

Create stable reference data used everywhere.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement master data management modules.

Backend APIs:
- Parent CRUD
  - Auto-generate Parent Unique ID
  - Soft delete using ACTIVE / INACTIVE status
- Classroom CRUD
  - Classroom name, age group, capacity, schedule
- Staff & Teacher management
  - Create Admin and Teacher users
  - Generate temporary username and password
  - First-login password reset

Admin Web:
- Ant Design tables and forms
- Add / edit / deactivate Parent, Classroom, Staff
- Show Parent ID and Staff credentials clearly

Design APIs so the mobile app can consume parent and classroom data later.

🟢 PHASE 3 – STUDENT MANAGEMENT + QR CODE
🎯 Goal

Core student system with QR attendance support.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement Student Management module.

Backend:
- Student CRUD
- Student must be linked to:
  - Parent
  - Classroom
- Auto-generate:
  - Student Unique ID
  - QR Code (store path or value in DB)
- Store student profile details:
  - Name, DOB, gender
  - Medical info
  - Photo
  - Birth certificate PDF
- Soft delete support

Admin Web:
- Student list table
- Student profile page
- QR code display
- Parent & Classroom selection dropdowns

Ensure QR code can be scanned by future mobile app.

🟢 PHASE 4 – ATTENDANCE SYSTEM (QR-BASED)
🎯 Goal

Automated attendance without manual registers.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement QR-based attendance system.

Backend:
- Attendance table
- API to mark attendance using QR scan
- Prevent duplicate check-in per day
- Store:
  - Check-in time
  - Check-out time
  - Date
- Attendance summary API

Admin Web:
- QR scan page (use device camera)
- Daily attendance list
- Attendance percentage calculation

Design APIs so both admin web and mobile app can use attendance data.

🟢 PHASE 5 – DASHBOARD & ANALYTICS
🎯 Goal

Visual system overview.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement Admin Dashboard.

Backend:
- APIs for:
  - Total students, parents, staff, classrooms
  - Today attendance percentage
  - Monthly payment percentage
  - Upcoming events

Admin Web:
- Ant Design dashboard layout
- Statistic cards
- Progress bars for attendance and payments
- Upcoming events list

Ensure calculations are reusable by mobile app.

🟢 PHASE 6 – NOTIFICATIONS & HOMEWORK
🎯 Goal

Internal communication system.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement Notifications and Homework modules.

Backend:
- Notification table with:
  - Title, message
  - Target role (PARENT, TEACHER, ALL)
  - Optional classroom
- Homework table:
  - Classroom
  - Title, description
  - Due date
  - Created by teacher

Admin Web:
- Create announcements
- View sent notifications
- Homework creation UI

Design notifications as internal system messages (no push service).

🟢 PHASE 7 – BILLING & EXPENSE MANAGEMENT
🎯 Goal

Financial tracking without online payment gateway.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Implement Billing and Expense Management.

Backend:
- Monthly billing records per student
- Billing status:
  - UNPAID
  - PENDING (receipt uploaded)
  - PAID (verified)
- Payment receipt upload
- Admin verification flow
- Expense tracking with category and date

Admin Web:
- Student billing list
- Payment verification screen
- Expense entry and monthly summary

Ensure parent mobile app can later view billing and upload receipts.

🟢 PHASE 8 – SECURITY, LOGS & POLISH
🎯 Goal

Production-ready behavior.

🧠 Antigravity Prompt
Finalize system security and stability.

Implement:
- Role-based access checks on all routes
- Input validation
- Audit logs for:
  - Login
  - Create / update / verify actions
- Soft delete everywhere
- Professional error messages

Admin Web:
- Handle empty states
- Loading states
- Permission-based UI hiding

Ensure APIs remain consistent for mobile app use.

